doctype html
html(lang="en")
  head
    title Web Scraper
    link(rel='stylesheet', href='/static/stylesheets/style.css')
    link(href='https://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Open+Sans|Fredoka+One', rel='stylesheet')
  body
    h1 Web Scraper
    h3 This web scraper app was originally created in  #[img(src='/static/img/node.png' width='120')]  as a command-line utility, which can be #[a(href='https://github.com/jeremybowden73/Webpage-Content-Scraper-using-node.js') found on GitHub here].
    h3 I've updated it as an Express app, deployed on Heroku. #[a(href='#') Here it is on GitHub].
    p Before this page loaded, the scraper had been busy scraping data from an e-commerce site #[a(href='http://shirts4mike.com/') http://shirts4mike.com/].
    p It scraped the following data for 8 shirts in the online store, and returned the here, ready to be loaded into this table.
    br
    .buttonDiv
      button(type='button') Back to jeremybowden.net
    br
    table#tableData
      each shirt in data
        tr
          each dataItem in shirt
            td= dataItem






